post2.content: What is a Boolean . The defention of a Boolean is a denoting a system of algebraic notation used to represent logical propositions, especially in computing and electronics. | A boolean expersions are either true or false | What do we use to represent them (Hint think of how domain/range of graph is answered) | . Examples . You have to be the age 16 or above to drive | Each cart can only hold 4 people | . Logical Operators . NOT, it displays the opposite of whatever the data is. Mainly used for true/false, and does not effect the variable. | AND, used to evaulte two conditions together and determine if both condintions are met | OR, only looks to see if one of the conditions is met | .
